an iranian official rejected us claims 
that his country was partly responsible for the us navys downing 
of an iranian jetliner and he said the navys presence in the 
persian gulf was to blame 
our civil airliner was using an internationally recognized air 
corridor used five times a week by the same captain iranian 
ambassador mohammad jaafar mahallati said friday 
during a naval skirmish with iranian gunboats the crew of the 
uss vincennes misinterpreted radar and electronic signals from the 
civilian airliner and shot it down july 3 killing all 290 people 
aboard 
conclusions of a us defense department investigation released 
friday blamed human error by the crew but defense secretary frank 
c carlucci said iran bore a heavy responsibility for letting the 
plane fly over a battle 
the report said several of the crews assumptions about the 
approaching flight were wrong including that it was descending 
toward the vincennes and was flying off course 
of the crews mistaken beliefs which the defense department 
released immediately after the disaster mahallati said 
in the view of the american administration when such 
incidents take place at the price of the lives of 290 people first 
you cannot provide the american people with facts it is better to 
forge information to misinform them than to keep quiet and wait 
until the facts come out 
the iranian envoy laid the blame on the us navys presence in 
the gulf 
one should conclude that the mere presence of such highly 
dangerous equipment which cannot be controlled even by trained 
american personnel is the source of tension he said by 
itself it can cause miseries one ofter the other 
