<TEXT>
lazarus salii the palau president who was found 
dead saturday from a gunshot to the head was described by a us 
state department official as a brilliant visionary 
he was a true leader of his people said james d berg 
director of the office of freely associated state affairs in 
washington dc 
salii was found dead in the living room of his home in koror 
palaus capital with a single gunshot to the head according to 
bonifacio basilius a presidential assistant 
it was the second violent death of a president in the tiny 
sparsely populated western pacific island chain in three years 
salii was elected president in august 1985 following the june 
30 1985 assassination of haruo remeliik palaus first president 
salii 54 was proamerican and a staunch supporter of a 
proposed compact of free association with the united states which 
would end palaus 41year un trusteeship status under the 
compact palau would become selfgoverning while retaining us 
economic assistance 
at his inauguration attended by pacific and us leaders salii 
spoke about the issues facing the nearly 15000 people who live on 
eight of palaus 200 islands which are roughly 800 miles south of 
guam and 600 miles east of the philippines 
salii had been involved in political status negotiations 
involving the thentrust territory of the pacific islands 
established by the united nations in 1947 
he was a member of the first unified micronesian commission and 
later was a palau representative to the congress of micronesia 
micronesia is an area of the pacific that includes palau the 
marshall islands the federated states of micronesia and the 
northern mariana islands all were part of the pacific trust 
territory 
the marshalls and the federated states of micronesia became 
freely associated states in 1986 after they approved compacts of 
free association the northern mariana islands became a 
commonwealth 
remeliik and salii were close friends remeliik named salii as 
his chief negotiator for a compact with the united states which 
administers palau 
he was a brilliant visionary on free association status 
said berg he was patient and persisted with a constant vision of 
his country as a sovereign nation in free association with the 
united states 
in washington dc janet mccoy principal interior department 
secretary said she was shocked and stunned and deeply grieved at 
president saliis passing it is a deep personal loss to the people 
of palau 
mrs mccoy was the last trust territory high commissioner the 
post was abolished in july 1987 she said she was a close friend of 
salii and enjoyed an excellent working relationship with him 
salii was a native of angaur the southernmost island in the 
palau group he graduated from the university of hawaii in 1961 
with a bachelors degree in political science and held numerous 
government positions prior to the presidency 
he is survived by his widow christina and several children 
